-- Oil Refineries in Port Arthur, Texas, Have Entergy Power Failure
-- B y   M o m i n g   Z h o u
-- 2013-04-14T17:49:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-14/oil-refineries-in-port-arthur-texas-have-entergy-power-failure.html
Total Petrochemicals USA Inc. and
Motiva Enterprises LLC were among the companies that reported
refinery flaring in  Port Arthur , Texas, due to a power failure,
according to recorded messages posted on the Southeast Texas
Alerting Network.  Flint Hills Resources LLC also reported a power failure at
its refining facilities in Port Arthur.  Entergy Corp., which supplies power to Port Arthur,
reported on its  website  that there were 11 outages in the area,
affecting 3,599 customers.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Moming Zhou at 
 mzhou29@bloomberg.net  